Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataBase
    The DataBase interface represents a general database and gives skeleton structure of methods every database must implement
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BooksDataBase
    The BooksDataBase class represents a data base holding books Records
    DataBaseAbstract
    The DataBaseAbstract class is an intermediate class for other database classes
    LibraryManagementSystem
    The LibraryManagementSystem class is a completely functioning library management system It is a composition of BooksDataBase and UsersDataBase,and SystemUsers Users can borrow or return books, staff can manage users and books
    LibraryStaff
    The LibraryStaff class represents library staff as a user of the Library Management System It contains such operations as adding or removing books and users All methods return String message indicating result of the request to the underlying database
    LibraryUser
    The LibraryUser class represents library user as a user of the Library Management System It contains such operations as borrowing or returning books All methods return String message indicating result of the request to the underlying database
    Main  
    Record
    The Record class represents a general n-fields wide database record
    SystemUser
    The SystemUser class represents a general user of the Library Management System It holds such user data as name,surname,password,status and books borrowed by the user It has accessors to the user' name,surname and status
    UsersDataBase
    The BooksDataBase class represents a data base holding users Records
